OL,3,CThe nurses who challenged their
OL,4,Cemployer after 'dignity violated'
OL,6,FA common theme though, is the desire -
OL,7,Fas they see it - to protect the safety
OL,8,Fof women in single sex spaces; not
OL,9,Fonly at their trust or within the NHS,
OL,10,Fbut in settings across the country.
OL,12,FOne told me: "I just thought it was
OL,13,Fimportant for me to stand up for
OL,14,Fwomen's rights and protect the women
OL,15,Faround me, for safety, dignity and all
OL,16,Fwomen out there."
OL,18,FThe issue arose when the women became
OL,19,Faware that a transgender colleague,
OL,20,Fcalled Rose Henderson, was using a
OL,21,Ffemale changing space.
